RACE.RACE_TEXT: LAUREL PARK RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 27300. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000, if for $12,500, allowed 4 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOTADA , nudged on soon after the break, sped up and took command leaving the chute, set a rated pace towards the rail, spurted away after being roused entering the lane, widened under a drive in mid stretch then was steadily hand ridden the final sixteenth. GWYNEDD , three deep prompting the pace, was under pressure into the lane, gave game chase from there and cut back into the margin a bit through the final seventy yards. HEART LIGHT bumped with a rival at the start, saved ground, was put to asking around the turn, chased into the lane and kept on with some effort while holding onto the show. MUSICAL CAT , bumped at the break, raced off the pace and three wide between foes into the turn, shifted out some for the drive and churned on. CLASSIC LYNNE was steadied back to last when in tight at the start, regrouped and was sent up between runners heading to the three quarter pole, tracked the winner from her outside, failed to kick on under pressure into the stretch and tired. HOLDING COURT , four wide between runners into the turn, dropped back. POET IN MY HEART , away alertly and flashed some speed, drafted back five wide outside rivals leaving the three quarter pole, failed to kick on into the far turn and faltered.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAM CHAR broke a step slow, regrouped and was sent up outside rivals in the opening furlong to take a short lead, handled inside pressure from FORTUNATA ITALIA, spurted away when given her cue approaching the quarter pole, kept on under solid handling past mid stretch and held firm to the wire. FORTUNATA ITALIA prompted the pace to the inside of the winner, steadied when in a bit close mid turn, shifted out in the drive and finished gamely. SWEET TALIA , off the pace and under asking around the turn, angled five wide into the lane and got by faders for the show. FANCY PRINCESS stalked the pace, raced four wide mid turn, failed to kick on nearing mid stretch and faded. BELLA BETTINA , three wide with pursuit, weakened in the drive. An objection by the rider of FORTUNATA ITALIA against the winner for alleged interference around the turn was not allowed. PER RULING #23-031 FROM THE MARYLAND RACING COMMISSION, TAM CHAR WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM 1st TO UNPLACED DUE TO A POSITIVE TEST.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LAUREL PARK RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 19130. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE AUGUST 3 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Weight, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 3 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOM TERRIFIC drafted well back in the opening furlong as a duel developed up front, came under pressure around the turn, edged up three wide into the lane, worked outward past mid stretch, leveled off under a drive and forged ahead in the final yards. BREITHORN , into the race at once, dueled inside a trio of rivals past the five sixteenths, shook clear under a drive in mid stretch, wandered outward a bit in deep stretch, kept on gamely but just could not fend off the winner's charge. JIMMY THE KID disputed the pace two wide between rivals, emerged as the closest pursuer past the eighth pole, stayed on well but settled for the show. BAHAMA CHANNEL dropped back off the pace while saving ground into the turn, swung six wide for the drive and was going well at the wire. ALL FOR LOVE , bumped at the break, saved ground off the duelers, edged up while saving ground in mid stretch then flattened out. NOMO RON , three deep attending the pace, battled between foes on near even terms past the five sixteenths, failed to kick on leaving mid stretch and weakened. CHROME FINISH lunged outward at the break and bumped with ALL FOR LOVE, corrected and hustled up to be in range four wide, came five wide under a ride into the lane and faded. BROOKS ROBINSON , four wide in range of the duelers into the turn, bid four deep mid turn, forced the issue to the head of the lane then succumbed.

Weight, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Other Than Maiden, Claiming Or Starter At A Mile Or Over Allowed 3 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIT MAZEL took over early then met an inside bid from BLUEBERRY INDIGO nearing the three quarter pole, went in tandem with that one for a furlong then was nudged on to separate into the turn, rated kindly while saving some ground past the three eighths, eased out some and responded when set down soon into the stretch, opened up under a solid drive in mid stretch then maintained a comfortable advantage while cruising through the final sixty yards. SHE IS WISKY settled four wide off the early pace, took closer order three wide nearing the lane, failed to kick on with the winner but kept on willingly to be well clear of the rest. DRY WELL saved ground early on, angled out leaving the far turn, circled four wide under a ride into the lane but lacked a serious finish. BLUEBERRY INDYGO , bumped at the break, moved up to the inside of the winner nearing the six furlong maker and contested the pace, rated back a bit nearing the turn, angled out and made another run mid turn, lacked a punch in upper stretch and faded through the final eighth. FLIMSY , bumped at the start, stalked the early pace, saved ground into the far turn, shifted out five wide for the drive and gave way.
